GitHub.

    - GitHub is the Repository.

    - GitHub is the Open Source Code.

    - It is maintained by Google.

    - Git is the tool used to interact with the Repository(GitHub).


download and install the Git.

website : https://git-scm.com/downloads

file name : Git-2.12.2.2-64-bit.exe


GitHub Operations.
-
1.Create the Repository (Locally)


2.Set the User Credentials

    - user name

    - user email


3.Adding the Files to the Repository

4.Commit the Files to the Repository

5.Creating the Branch

6.Checkout the Branch

7.Commit the Files in Branch

8.Merging

9.Interacting the Cloud

10.Integrating the GitHub Repository to the IDE'S  -- WebStrom , Ecilipse , Visual Studio

11.Push the Code to the Cloud Repository.

12.Pull the Code From the Cloud Repository.


Creating the Repository Locally.

    - Create the Folder in any drive

        Ex.
            demo

    - rigth click the demo folder --> select "Git Bash Here"

    - Execite the Following Command.

        $git init


    [ Note. Automatically "demo folder" converted as "local repository"]



Adding the User Credentials.

    - $ git config --global user.name '**********'

    - $ git config --global user.email '*********'


Create the Files in Repository.

    - $ touch index.html

    [Automatically 'index.html' created in 'demo repository']


Status Of the Git Files.

    - $ git status


Adding the Files to the Repository.

    - $git add index.html


Commit the Files to the Repository.

    - git commit

    - press i

    - type "initial commit"

    - press esc

    - type ":wq"

    - press enter

 From Second Commit Onwards Follow the Below Steps.

    - modify the index.html

    - $git add .

    - $git commit -m "Message"


 Creating the Branch.

    - $ git branch my_branch

 Checkout the Branch

    - $git checkout my_branch


 Merge the Code.

    $git checkout master

    $git merge my_branch

































